<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F52FEDE48A752E9FE2BFF5F" lastPageId="286" lastPageNumber="287" pageId="284" pageNumber="285" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418F52FEDC48A752E9FD31F825" blockId="284.[151,1437,1477,2005]" pageId="284" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F52FEDC48A752E9FE0DFA2D" bold="true" box="[151,424,1477,1502]" pageId="284" pageNumber="285">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 4.7–7.0 mm. Completely testaceous, except petiole black. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 10:5:45:30:26:15:11:10:8:10. Head flat, shiny, weakly granulated; temple unsculptured; frontal line complete; occipital carina incomplete, only present behind ocellar triangle and shortly on sides; POL = 2; OL = 4.5; OOL = 8.5; OPL = 2.5; temple prominent. Pronotum flat, shiny, with a weak posterior transverse impression; posterior collar very short; pronotum unsculptured, except some longitudinal keels on lateral regions and some short keels on posterior transverse impression; pronotal tubercle not reaching tegula. Scutum dull, granulated and with some little distinct areolae. Notauli hardly distinct, incomplete, shortly present near anterior margin of scutum. Scutellum and metanotum shiny, punctate, unsculptured among punctures, or weakly alutaceous. Propodeum (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F52FEDC4A8651C9FC8FF90D" box="[694,810,1765,1789]" captionStart="PLATE 81" captionStartId="285.[151,232,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[222,1365,213,1812]" captionTargetId="figure-91@285.[202,1384,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="285" captionText="PLATE 81. A, B, C, F. Chelae, holotypes. D. Propodeum of holotype in lateral view. E. Profemur and protibia of holotype. A. Dryinus nanlingensis (from Xu et al. 2012b). B. D. ornatus (from Olmi 1993d). C. D. parvulus (from Olmi 1987a). D–F. D. praeclarus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.36 mm for A, 0.27 mm for B and C, 0.71 mm for D, 0.86 mm for E and 0.30 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278660" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278660/files/figure.png" pageId="284" pageNumber="285">Plate 81D</figureCitation>
) reticulate rugose, without transverse or longitudinal keels; dorsal surface more than twice as long as posterior surface (27:10). Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein much longer than proximal part (26:9). Profemur with stalk approximately as long as club (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F52FEDC49C4507DFDC5F899" box="[500,608,1873,1897]" captionStart="PLATE 81" captionStartId="285.[151,232,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[222,1365,213,1812]" captionTargetId="figure-91@285.[202,1384,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="285" captionText="PLATE 81. A, B, C, F. Chelae, holotypes. D. Propodeum of holotype in lateral view. E. Profemur and protibia of holotype. A. Dryinus nanlingensis (from Xu et al. 2012b). B. D. ornatus (from Olmi 1993d). C. D. parvulus (from Olmi 1987a). D–F. D. praeclarus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.36 mm for A, 0.27 mm for B and C, 0.71 mm for D, 0.86 mm for E and 0.30 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278660" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278660/files/figure.png" pageId="284" pageNumber="285">Plate 81E</figureCitation>
); protibia very slender and slightly curved (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F52FEDC4C7D507DFB1CF899" box="[1101,1209,1873,1897]" captionStart="PLATE 81" captionStartId="285.[151,232,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[222,1365,213,1812]" captionTargetId="figure-91@285.[202,1384,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="285" captionText="PLATE 81. A, B, C, F. Chelae, holotypes. D. Propodeum of holotype in lateral view. E. Profemur and protibia of holotype. A. Dryinus nanlingensis (from Xu et al. 2012b). B. D. ornatus (from Olmi 1993d). C. D. parvulus (from Olmi 1987a). D–F. D. praeclarus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.36 mm for A, 0.27 mm for B and C, 0.71 mm for D, 0.86 mm for E and 0.30 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278660" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278660/files/figure.png" pageId="284" pageNumber="285">Plate 81E</figureCitation>
) Protarsal segments in following proportions: 32:3.5:5:20:26. Enlarged claw not spatulate (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F52FEDC4B8D5059FB8CF87D" box="[957,1065,1909,1933]" captionStart="PLATE 81" captionStartId="285.[151,232,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[222,1365,213,1812]" captionTargetId="figure-91@285.[202,1384,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="285" captionText="PLATE 81. A, B, C, F. Chelae, holotypes. D. Propodeum of holotype in lateral view. E. Profemur and protibia of holotype. A. Dryinus nanlingensis (from Xu et al. 2012b). B. D. ornatus (from Olmi 1993d). C. D. parvulus (from Olmi 1987a). D–F. D. praeclarus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.36 mm for A, 0.27 mm for B and C, 0.71 mm for D, 0.86 mm for E and 0.30 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278660" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278660/files/figure.png" pageId="284" pageNumber="285">Plate 81F</figureCitation>
) with one strong subdistal tooth and one row of 12 lamellae. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F52FEDC4ACB50B5FCC2F841" box="[763,871,1945,1969]" captionStart="PLATE 81" captionStartId="285.[151,232,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[222,1365,213,1812]" captionTargetId="figure-91@285.[202,1384,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="285" captionText="PLATE 81. A, B, C, F. Chelae, holotypes. D. Propodeum of holotype in lateral view. E. Profemur and protibia of holotype. A. Dryinus nanlingensis (from Xu et al. 2012b). B. D. ornatus (from Olmi 1993d). C. D. parvulus (from Olmi 1987a). D–F. D. praeclarus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.36 mm for A, 0.27 mm for B and C, 0.71 mm for D, 0.86 mm for E and 0.30 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278660" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278660/files/figure.png" pageId="284" pageNumber="285">Plate 81F</figureCitation>
) with two rows of about 21 lamellae; distal apex with about seven lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
